Recolonization was detected after 30 min on the skin with plastic drape and after 60 min on the skin without plastic drape (Figure 3
). All bacterial cultures were CoNS, but three samples exhibited CoNS mixed with diphteroid rods. None of the cultures showed any growth of S. 
aureus. Before antiseptic preparation with 0.5% chlorhexidine in 70% ethanol, all skin samples (n = 10) displayed growth of CoNS. All cultures from the anterior nares showed growth of CoNS but none of S. aureus. The sedimentation agar plates exposed to the OR environment for 6 hr contained 17 and 23 colonies of CoNS, respectively.
